				{
					"id": "231059",
					"author": {
						"name": "nitrag",
						"key": "nitrag",
						"displayName": "Ryan Gartin",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/New_York"
					},
					"body": "This works in 2.1.4-GA. However, when I switch to 3.0.0-beta it defaults to entire black tab color settings. \r\n\r\n2.1.4-GA - http://imgur.com/duJKj\r\n3.0.0-20121207 - http://imgur.com/TNlPJ",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "nitrag",
						"key": "nitrag",
						"displayName": "Ryan Gartin",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/New_York"
					},
					"created": "2012-12-12T19:08:20.000+0000",
					"updated": "2012-12-12T19:08:20.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "440613",
					"author": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "Issue can still be seen in SDK version {{7.3.0.v20180807095741}}. {{TabGroup.backgroundColor}} works on iOS but not on Android. \r\n\r\n*Test Case*\r\n{code:java}\r\nvar win1 = Ti.UI.createWindow({\r\n    backgroundColor: 'blue',\r\n    title: 'Blue'\r\n});\r\nwin1.add(Ti.UI.createLabel({text: 'I am a blue window.'}));\r\n\r\nvar win2 = Ti.UI.createWindow({\r\n    backgroundColor: 'red',\r\n    title: 'Red'\r\n});\r\nwin2.add(Ti.UI.createLabel({text: 'I am a red window.'}));\r\n\r\nvar tab1 = Ti.UI.createTab({\r\n    window: win1,\r\n    title: 'Blue'\r\n}),\r\ntab2 = Ti.UI.createTab({\r\n    window: win2,\r\n    title: 'Red'\r\n}),\r\ntabGroup = Ti.UI.createTabGroup({\r\n    tabs: [tab1, tab2]\r\n        \r\n});\r\ntabGroup.backgroundColor = 'red';\r\ntabGroup.open();{code}\r\n\r\n\r\n*Test Environment*\r\n{code:java}\r\nAPPC Studio: 5.0.0.201712081732\r\nAPPC CLI: 7.0.4\r\nNexus 6p Emulator (7.1)\r\nIphone 6 Simul\r\nOperating System Name: Mac OS High Sierra\r\nOperating System Version: 10.13\r\nNode.js Version: 8.9.1\r\nXcode 9.2\r\n{code}\r\n",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"created": "2018-08-09T14:02:27.000+0000",
					"updated": "2018-08-09T14:02:27.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "440614",
					"author": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "Although looking at the Appc docs https://docs.appcelerator.com/platform/latest/#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup-property-tabsBackgroundColor {{tabsBackgroundColor}} can be used and can confirm works on both iOS and Android.",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"created": "2018-08-09T14:25:56.000+0000",
					"updated": "2018-08-09T14:25:56.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "442405",
					"author": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "Using the following code we can see that setting {{tabsBackgroundColor}} to blue only shows on iOS.\r\n{code:java}\r\nvar tabGroup = Ti.UI.createTabGroup({\r\n  tabsBackgroundColor: 'blue'\r\n});\r\n \r\ntabGroup.open();\r\n{code}\r\n !Screenshot 2018-10-08 at 14.52.15.png|thumbnail! ",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "smohammed",
						"key": "smohammed",
						"displayName": "Samir Mohammed",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"created": "2018-10-08T14:19:53.000+0000",
					"updated": "2018-10-08T14:19:53.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "446642",
					"author": {
						"name": "amdolan",
						"key": "amdolan",
						"displayName": "amdolan",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "I have no issues with the following config:\r\n\r\ntiapp.xml: \r\n{code}<sdk-version>8.0.0.v20190307063026</sdk-version>{code}\r\n\r\napp.tss:\r\n{code}\r\n'TabGroup[platform=android]': {\r\n\tstyle: Ti.UI.Android.TABS_STYLE_BOTTOM_NAVIGATION,\r\n\ttabsBackgroundColor: \"blue\"\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSorry I don't know how to add a screenshot but the background is blue.",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "amdolan",
						"key": "amdolan",
